<center class="home">
<h1>Aircrafts Of Airforce</h1>
<img src="https://media.gettyimages.com/photos/indian-air-force-miraj-2000-fighters-and-sukhoi-jets-fly-past-during-picture-id1174362760?k=20&m=1174362760&s=612x612&w=0&h=Uj7mzSIQo8d5ad-m52R8w8aTf0N3fRzu2pjNnMVau4I=" style="text-align:center;padding:40px 10px 50px 10px;filter:saturate(80%);filter:brightness(101%);" width="500px" height="350px">
<p>
The Indian Airforce has a huge number of aircrafts in use all serving different roles.Here is a list of all the aircracts:-<br>  
</p>
<h2>Dassault Rafale</h2>
<button type="button" class="collapsible"><img src="https://media.gettyimages.com/photos/french-rafale-fighter-jet-approach-to-the-french-aircraft-carrier-de-picture-id1200174837?k=20&m=1200174837&s=612x612&w=0&h=c6stT0E0i4EaY0_qZMSmRxYEYGJd4w57X7spB1UAg8s=" style="text-align:center;padding:40px 10px 50px 10px;filter:saturate(80%);filter:brightness(101%);" width="350px" height="250px"></button>
  <div class="a_cont"><p>The Dassault Rafale (French pronunciation:, literally meaning "gust of wind",and "burst of fire" in a more military sense) is a French twin-engine, canard delta wing, multirole fighter aircraft designed and built by Dassault Aviation. Equipped with a wide range of weapons, the Rafale is intended to perform air supremacy, interdiction, aerial reconnaissance, ground support, in-depth strike, anti-ship strike and nuclear deterrence missions. The Rafale is referred to as an "omnirole" aircraft by Dassault.
  </p></div>
<h2>Sukhoi Su-30</h2>
<button type="button" class="collapsible"><img src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/76/Sukhoi_Su-30SM_in_flight_2014.jpg/450px-Sukhoi_Su-30SM_in_flight_2014.jpg" style="text-align:center;padding:40px 10px 50px 10px;filter:saturate(80%);filter:brightness(101%);" width="350px" height="250px"></button>
  <div class="a_cont"><p>The Sukhoi Su-30 (Russian: Сухой Су-30; NATO reporting name: Flanker-C/G/H) is a twin-engine, two-seat supermaneuverable fighter aircraft developed in the Soviet Union by Russia's Sukhoi Aviation Corporation. It is a multirole fighter for all-weather, air-to-air and air interdiction missions.</p></div>
<h2>HAL Tejas</h2>
<button type="button" class="collapsible"><img src="https://media.gettyimages.com/photos/tejas-multirole-light-fighter-designed-by-the-aeronautical-agency-a-picture-id1126586238?k=20&m=1126586238&s=612x612&w=0&h=mzLQ4bMWtp7qOj9scNXKHq3jq5csFUhM9WTmuyL1ugM=" style="text-align:center;padding:40px 10px 50px 10px;filter:saturate(80%);filter:brightness(101%);" width="350px" height="250px"></button>
  <div class="a_cont"><p>The HAL Tejas is an Indian multirole light fighter designed by the Aeronautical Development Agency (ADA) in collaboration with Aircraft Research and Design Centre (ARDC) of Hindustan Aeronautics Limited (HAL) for the Indian Air Force and Indian Navy.It came from the Light Combat Aircraft (LCA) programme, which began in the 1980s to replace India's ageing MiG-21 fighters.In 2003, the LCA was officially named "Tejas".It is the smallest and lightest in its class of contemporary supersonic combat aircraft.</p></div>
<h2>MiG-29</h2>
<button type="button" class="collapsible"><img src="https://media.gettyimages.com/photos/an-mig29-lands-at-adampur-air-base-during-preparations-ahead-of-air-picture-id1044523884?k=20&m=1044523884&s=612x612&w=0&h=RfsNrL2nnmCJ7Aex9iwXlFsiQv0IWaNL_qUXkdTFdgI=" style="text-align:center;padding:40px 10px 50px 10px;filter:saturate(80%);filter:brightness(101%);" width="350px" height="250px"></button>
  <div class="a_cont"><p>The Mikoyan MiG-29 (Russian: Микоян МиГ-29; NATO reporting name: Fulcrum) is a twin-engine jet fighter aircraft designed in the Soviet Union. Developed by the Mikoyan design bureau as an air superiority fighter during the 1970s, the MiG-29, along with the larger Sukhoi Su-27, was developed to counter new U.S. fighters such as the McDonnell Douglas F-15 Eagle and the General Dynamics F-16 Fighting Falcon.he MiG-29 entered service with the Soviet Air Forces in 1982.</p></div>
  <h2>Mirage 2000</h2>
<button type="button" class="collapsible"><img src="https://media.gettyimages.com/photos/french-airforce-dassault-mirage-2000-in-the-flyingdisplay-with-smoke-picture-id973362982?k=20&m=973362982&s=612x612&w=0&h=6AI4SLQs3FD3DWNMDmZT4KKYEv1fRjuXwKBIH6i_g9U=" style="text-align:center;padding:40px 10px 50px 10px;filter:saturate(80%);filter:brightness(101%);" width="350px" height="250px"></button>
  <div class="a_cont"><p>The Dassault Mirage 2000 is a French multirole, single-engine, fourth-generation jet fighter manufactured by Dassault Aviation. It was designed in the late 1970s as a lightweight fighter to replace the Mirage III for the French Air Force (Armée de l'air). The Mirage 2000 evolved into a multirole aircraft with several variants developed, with sales to a number of nations. It was later developed into the Mirage 2000N and 2000D strike variants, the improved Mirage 2000-5, and several export variants. Over 600 aircraft were built and it has been in service with 9 nations</p></div>
  <h2>SEPECAT Jaguar</h2>
<button type="button" class="collapsible"><img src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/71/Jaguar_DF-SD-05-05511.JPEG/450px-Jaguar_DF-SD-05-05511.JPEG" style="text-align:center;padding:40px 10px 50px 10px;filter:saturate(80%);filter:brightness(101%);" width="350px" height="250px"></button>
  <div class="a_cont"><p>The SEPECAT Jaguar is an Anglo-French jet attack aircraft originally used by the British Royal Air Force and the French Air Force in the close air support and nuclear strike role. It is still in service with the Indian Air Force</p></div>
  <h2>MiG-21 bison</h2>
<button type="button" class="collapsible"><img src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/86/Sheeju_mig21.JPG/330px-Sheeju_mig21.JPG" style="text-align:center;padding:40px 10px 50px 10px;filter:saturate(80%);filter:brightness(101%);" width="350px" height="250px"></button>
  <div class="a_cont"><p>The Mikoyan-Gurevich MiG-21 (Russian: Микоян и Гуревич МиГ-21; NATO reporting name: Fishbed) is a supersonic jet fighter and interceptor aircraft, designed by the Mikoyan-Gurevich Design Bureau in the Soviet Union. Its nicknames include: "balalaika", because its planform resembles the stringed musical instrument of the same name; "Ołówek", Polish for "pencil", due to the shape of its fuselage,and "Én Bạc", meaning "silver swallow", in Vietnamese.</p></div>
</center>
<script>
var coll = document.getElementsByClassName("collapsible");
var i;

for (i = 0; i < coll.length; i++) {
  coll[i].addEventListener("click", function() {
    this.classList.toggle("active");
    var content = this.nextElementSibling;
    if (content.style.display === "block") {
      content.style.display = "none";
    } else {
      content.style.display = "block";
    }
  });
}
</script>
</body>
</html>